The continuation token passed to `Page.FromValues(...)` is using `nextPage` (the URI used to fetch the current page), not the `NextLink` returned by the service for the *next* page. This breaks manual paging/resume scenarios because `Page.ContinuationToken` will point back to the current page and can cause re-fetching the same page repeatedly. Use `result.NextLink` (converted to string) when constructing the `Page<T>`.
```suggestion
                Uri nextLink = result.NextLink;

